WEBVTT

1
00:02:17.611 --> 00:02:22.866
(High Valyrian)

2
00:02:28.163 --> 00:02:29.498
What?

3
00:02:34.127 --> 00:02:35.504
I can't understand.

4
00:02:46.932 --> 00:02:48.433
Speak plainly.

5
00:02:54.148 --> 00:02:55.482
Stop.

6
00:02:56.024 --> 00:02:57.359
Stop it.

7
00:03:29.433 --> 00:03:30.726
- There's been a raven.
- There's been a raven.

8
00:03:35.856 --> 00:03:37.358
Good morrow. Your Grace.

9
00:03:38.442 --> 00:03:40.945
Slept well. I trust?

10
00:03:41.821 --> 00:03:43.697
As I said. there's been a raven.

11
00:03:46.659 --> 00:03:49.912
Aegon's army departed
King's Landing a fortnight ago.

12
00:03:50.037 --> 00:03:54.917
The castles of Rosby and Stokeworth
have both fallen without siege.

13
00:03:55.376 --> 00:03:57.044
They have raised Aegon's banner

14
00:03:57.378 --> 00:04:00.673
and added their levies
to Ser Criston Cole's host.

15
00:04:01.716 --> 00:04:03.551
Both houses cited that

16
00:04:04.427 --> 00:04:07.847
sad business with the usurper's son
in their declarations.

17
00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:10.641
Ser Criston's army

18
00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:13.144
now tripled in strength

19
00:04:13.853 --> 00:04:16.063
might have Harrenhal
as its destination.

20
00:04:16.856 --> 00:04:19.942
Even if you can raise
a host of Rivermen

21
00:04:20.067 --> 00:04:22.653
they will not be ready
in time to face him.

22
00:04:29.327 --> 00:04:31.746
Let's see what your Lord Paramount
is made of.

23
00:04:37.835 --> 00:04:39.379
M-M-My prince...

24
00:04:39.462 --> 00:04:40.838
M-My grace.

25
00:04:41.172 --> 00:04:42.215
Your Grace.

26
00:04:43.549 --> 00:04:46.761
Lord Grover is looking more hale
and healthy than I expected.

27
00:04:46.886 --> 00:04:49.305
This is Ser Oscar Tully.
grandson to Grover Tully.

28
00:04:49.389 --> 00:04:50.932
He is heir to Riverrun

29
00:04:51.015 --> 00:04:53.601
and the future Lord Paramount
of the Riverlands.

30
00:04:54.144 --> 00:04:57.647
His Grace. the King Consort.
Daemon Targaryen.

31
00:04:57.730 --> 00:05:00.316
- It is an honor. Your Grace.
- Indeed.

32
00:05:06.865 --> 00:05:08.575
How fares your grandsire?

33
00:05:12.954 --> 00:05:15.707
Sadly. he remains incapacitated.

34
00:05:16.207 --> 00:05:18.793
He lies in a kind of waking sleep

35
00:05:18.877 --> 00:05:21.880
unable to do much more
than take meager drink.

36
00:05:22.505 --> 00:05:24.549
It is barely enough to sustain him.

37
00:05:25.133 --> 00:05:26.635
So. he's alive?

38
00:05:27.135 --> 00:05:29.095
Yes. gods be good.

39
00:05:29.387 --> 00:05:32.057
Well. my time is short
and I have need of an army.

40
00:05:32.140 --> 00:05:34.351
Perhaps you might place
a feather pillow over his head

41
00:05:34.434 --> 00:05:36.394
and speed along your inheritance?

42
00:05:38.688 --> 00:05:42.275
I love my grandsire. like a father.

43
00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:46.488
My own lord father died suddenly.
himself a young man.

44
00:05:47.364 --> 00:05:49.908
Lord Grover raised me in his stead.

45
00:05:49.991 --> 00:05:51.368
All very touching.

46
00:05:51.451 --> 00:05:53.245
Are you here to speak
with your grandsire's voice?

47
00:05:53.495 --> 00:05:55.372
For House Tully and the Riverlands?

48
00:05:55.539 --> 00:05:56.957
While he still lives?

49
00:05:59.584 --> 00:06:02.921
- That is not our way.
- Then you're of no use to me.

50
00:06:04.256 --> 00:06:05.799
I can see why the Blackwoods
and the Brackens

51
00:06:05.883 --> 00:06:07.134
did not fear to start a war

52
00:06:07.217 --> 00:06:09.177
beneath the nose
of their liege lords.

53
00:06:09.595 --> 00:06:11.680
House Tully is a fish with no head.

54
00:06:11.972 --> 00:06:15.726
Remind me which of your countrymen
claim to fight in the name of Aegon?

55
00:06:15.809 --> 00:06:18.020
Was it... was it Bracken
or Blackwood?

56
00:06:18.103 --> 00:06:20.606
It was House Bracken
that declared Green. Your Grace.

57
00:06:20.898 --> 00:06:22.024
Who could remember.

58
00:06:23.108 --> 00:06:24.151
Summon the Blackwoods here.

59
00:06:24.234 --> 00:06:26.945
I require men of action
to lead my host of Rivermen.

60
00:06:56.058 --> 00:06:57.434
M'lady.

61
00:07:01.063 --> 00:07:04.024
"Princess."
if we're holding to formalities.

62
00:07:04.900 --> 00:07:07.194
Apologies. Princess.

63
00:07:09.030 --> 00:07:10.906
And you are Alyn.

64
00:07:11.240 --> 00:07:13.325
Yes. Princess.

65
00:07:14.910 --> 00:07:17.663
I'm given to understand
my lord husband owes you his life.

66
00:07:21.751 --> 00:07:24.629
But I was not told
his savior was so comely.

67
00:07:25.922 --> 00:07:28.007
Your mother must've been
very beautiful.

68
00:07:28.216 --> 00:07:29.467
Rhaenys.

69
00:07:38.184 --> 00:07:40.353
- Is your work finished?
- No. m'lord.

70
00:07:51.572 --> 00:07:53.533
I just had a word with your captains.

71
00:07:55.994 --> 00:07:59.372
He was the sailor who plucked you
from your watery grave?

72
00:08:06.921 --> 00:08:08.256
Yes.

73
00:08:09.507 --> 00:08:11.259
You did not think to mention it?

74
00:08:12.093 --> 00:08:13.845
I did not think it relevant.

75
00:08:16.139 --> 00:08:18.057
I know who he is. Corlys.

76
00:08:20.518 --> 00:08:22.937
Alyn's past is no fault of his.

77
00:08:24.147 --> 00:08:25.315
He saved his lord's life.

78
00:08:25.398 --> 00:08:27.817
He should be raised up and honored.
not hidden beneath the tides.

79
00:08:27.901 --> 00:08:29.444
Is this why you came?

80
00:08:30.987 --> 00:08:32.655
To subject me to an inquisition?

81
00:08:34.949 --> 00:08:38.370
I came to tell you that Baela
has called me to Dragonstone.

82
00:08:38.787 --> 00:08:40.121
Baela?

83
00:08:41.164 --> 00:08:43.750
That council is going to dine on her
and Jace for supper.

84
00:08:43.833 --> 00:08:46.169
They grow restless
in Rhaenyra's absence.

85
00:08:46.294 --> 00:08:49.339
Still. where has that woman gone?

86
00:08:49.422 --> 00:08:52.467
I suspect to try and draw us all
back from the abyss.

87
00:09:15.073 --> 00:09:18.493
- Good morrow. Your Grace.
- Good morrow. Grand Maester.

88
00:09:22.080 --> 00:09:23.415
As requested.

89
00:09:24.708 --> 00:09:27.252
- I brewed it myself.
- Thank you.

90
00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:30.214
I will see it delivered discreetly.

91
00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:36.094
Do report if the recipient
has need of any remedy.

92
00:09:36.178 --> 00:09:38.430
The tea is known
to disagree with the gut.

93
00:09:39.389 --> 00:09:41.016
I shall observe the girl closely.

94
00:09:48.023 --> 00:09:49.358
Grand Maester.

95
00:09:55.698 --> 00:09:57.783
You've ever been a practical man

96
00:09:58.117 --> 00:10:00.160
an honorable servant to the crown.

97
00:10:01.412 --> 00:10:04.039
And you served my lord husband
in his darkest hours.

98
00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:06.792
Such was my duty. Your Grace.

99
00:10:08.752 --> 00:10:10.087
Tell me.

100
00:10:12.214 --> 00:10:14.925
Do you believe Viserys wanted
Aegon to succeed him?

101
00:10:19.722 --> 00:10:21.765
I could not know.

102
00:10:23.809 --> 00:10:26.395
His Grace never raised
the matter with me.

103
00:11:26.497 --> 00:11:29.459
Ser Criston Cole's host has taken
to exploiting the tree cover

104
00:11:29.542 --> 00:11:30.752
to conceal its movements.

105
00:11:30.835 --> 00:11:33.588
He now only travels by night
to confound our dragons.

106
00:11:33.671 --> 00:11:35.423
And what is Cole's heading?

107
00:11:35.715 --> 00:11:37.300
It is difficult to say.
but there were signs

108
00:11:37.383 --> 00:11:40.178
of an army moving northwest.
I believe.

109
00:11:40.553 --> 00:11:41.763
She believes.

110
00:11:41.846 --> 00:11:43.598
You should've burned them
when you had the chance.

111
00:11:43.807 --> 00:11:45.058
Perhaps you can. Ser Alfred

112
00:11:45.141 --> 00:11:46.935
when you next sight them
on your dragon.

113
00:11:47.852 --> 00:11:51.689
The only reason we know any of this
is because of Baela's efforts.

114
00:11:51.773 --> 00:11:53.316
What do we know. my prince?

115
00:11:53.525 --> 00:11:55.694
If you ask me. it is little and less.

116
00:11:55.777 --> 00:11:58.446
We know that Cole possesses a host
that is growing in strength

117
00:11:58.530 --> 00:11:59.781
and that it is a problem.

118
00:11:59.864 --> 00:12:02.659
Can Daemon hope to meet it
with his own in time?

119
00:12:02.742 --> 00:12:03.952
And if I know the Riverlands

120
00:12:04.035 --> 00:12:05.996
he has more disentangling
ahead of him

121
00:12:06.079 --> 00:12:09.082
than the end of a Lyseni orgy.

122
00:12:09.291 --> 00:12:12.085
Have you heard word from your father?

123
00:12:15.338 --> 00:12:16.423
No.

124
00:12:16.506 --> 00:12:18.383
Ravens were sent to Harrenhal

125
00:12:18.466 --> 00:12:21.803
seeking news of Daemon's progress
with the Riverlords.

126
00:12:21.887 --> 00:12:24.347
None have. as yet. returned.

127
00:12:24.473 --> 00:12:25.807
Just so.

128
00:12:26.141 --> 00:12:28.477
An enemy host.
growing in constitution

129
00:12:28.560 --> 00:12:33.440
marches somewhere in the vastness
of the Crownlands.

130
00:12:33.523 --> 00:12:36.651
We could. perhaps. act
if only we had a host of our own.

131
00:12:37.069 --> 00:12:38.570
Or someone here to lead us.

132
00:12:39.112 --> 00:12:41.156
Mind your tongue. Ser Alfred.

133
00:12:42.491 --> 00:12:44.660
Does it speak falsely. my prince?

134
00:12:44.910 --> 00:12:46.870
This council is rudderless.

135
00:12:47.412 --> 00:12:49.706
I'm doing my best to steer it.
Ser Alfred.

136
00:12:51.458 --> 00:12:54.836
Why should your voice
be any louder than ours. Princess?

137
00:12:54.962 --> 00:12:56.713
The queen did not name you Hand.

138
00:12:56.922 --> 00:12:59.258
It is her voice.
and that of the king consort

139
00:12:59.341 --> 00:13:02.553
that we need to raise alliances
and command our vassals.

140
00:13:02.636 --> 00:13:05.264
- But they are gone.
- What has come of this council?

141
00:13:10.811 --> 00:13:12.146
My lord.

142
00:13:15.524 --> 00:13:18.277
Our enemy is on the march.

143
00:13:18.861 --> 00:13:20.863
Is there naught to be done
in the absence of the queen

144
00:13:20.946 --> 00:13:24.199
but to grouse and claw for power?

145
00:13:30.289 --> 00:13:32.499
We do not know the queen's doings.

146
00:13:33.834 --> 00:13:37.922
But we must trust that she seeks
the same as each of us at this table.

147
00:13:40.132 --> 00:13:42.051
An end to this conflict.

148
00:14:04.407 --> 00:14:06.200
Men of House Darklyn.

149
00:14:06.867 --> 00:14:09.745
All who bend the knee
to the true king. Aegon

150
00:14:09.829 --> 00:14:10.997
will be spared.

151
00:14:12.081 --> 00:14:14.792
You can earn back your honor
by raising his banner

152
00:14:14.876 --> 00:14:18.921
and fighting in his name
against the Whore of Dragonstone.

153
00:14:20.173 --> 00:14:21.674
All who refuse...

154
00:14:23.634 --> 00:14:25.011
will have their death.

155
00:14:39.692 --> 00:14:41.235
Good morrow. Lord Darklyn.

156
00:14:42.070 --> 00:14:44.906
Is there no honor left
in this world. Cole?

157
00:14:45.615 --> 00:14:49.661
Sacking your queen's own castles
and putting her people to the sword?

158
00:14:50.495 --> 00:14:51.871
"Kingmaker."

159
00:14:56.459 --> 00:14:58.920
You're not fit for the white cloak.

160
00:15:02.298 --> 00:15:04.843
This is a better death
than a traitor deserves.

161
00:15:05.802 --> 00:15:07.220
You should thank me for it.

162
00:15:10.181 --> 00:15:12.600
Yours will come in kind.

163
00:15:27.657 --> 00:15:28.992
Lord Hand.

164
00:15:44.382 --> 00:15:48.011
We'll lead the van northeast.
follow the coastline.

165
00:15:49.513 --> 00:15:51.264
I realize you were
neither born nor bred

166
00:15:51.348 --> 00:15:53.934
anywhere near the Crownlands.
my good Lord Hand

167
00:15:54.601 --> 00:15:56.812
but Harrenhal is to the west.

168
00:16:01.108 --> 00:16:02.567
Indeed it is.

169
00:16:05.696 --> 00:16:07.030
Fuck you.

170
00:16:07.197 --> 00:16:08.740
I told you
we should've sent our dragons.

171
00:16:08.824 --> 00:16:10.325
And now look what's happened.

172
00:16:11.201 --> 00:16:13.787
Daemon. of all people.
has taken Harrenhal.

173
00:16:14.037 --> 00:16:16.415
I give you a job.
and now you just sit there.

174
00:16:16.498 --> 00:16:18.083
It's your fucking castle!

175
00:16:20.711 --> 00:16:24.423
Well. that castle is more crippled
than I am. Your Grace.

176
00:16:26.008 --> 00:16:27.426
It's like to drive Daemon to madness

177
00:16:27.509 --> 00:16:28.844
as he attempts to make use of it.

178
00:16:28.927 --> 00:16:30.804
It is beyond his faculties.

179
00:16:32.097 --> 00:16:35.809
It is also penniless.
as I happily control all of its gold.

180
00:16:36.101 --> 00:16:39.521
So. as Harrenhal
saps Daemon's resolve

181
00:16:39.605 --> 00:16:41.815
the false queen remains
trapped on her island

182
00:16:41.899 --> 00:16:45.569
and Ser Criston continues
felling castles in the Crownlands.

183
00:16:48.072 --> 00:16:50.491
I need to be informed of these things

184
00:16:50.741 --> 00:16:52.284
if I am to make informed rulings.

185
00:16:52.368 --> 00:16:55.204
I will not be made to look a fool
in front of my allies and enemies.

186
00:16:55.287 --> 00:16:56.747
Harrenhal must wait.

187
00:17:00.668 --> 00:17:02.837
Ser Criston is marching
on Rook's Rest.

188
00:17:03.587 --> 00:17:05.422
Rook's... A pathetic prize.

189
00:17:05.506 --> 00:17:07.466
- I gave no such command...
- The castle is small

190
00:17:08.801 --> 00:17:10.094
weakly defended

191
00:17:10.427 --> 00:17:12.888
and Lord Staunton
sits on Rhaenyra's council.

192
00:17:13.514 --> 00:17:15.099
After Cole smashes it

193
00:17:15.391 --> 00:17:17.935
we'll have Dragonstone
effectively cut off by land.

194
00:17:19.478 --> 00:17:21.731
This war will not be won
with dragons alone

195
00:17:22.356 --> 00:17:25.318
but with dragons flying
behind armies of men.

196
00:17:25.401 --> 00:17:26.444
No!

197
00:17:26.736 --> 00:17:29.071
Have him turnabout.
I want Harrenhal back.

198
00:17:30.364 --> 00:17:32.408
Cole is already preparing his attack.

199
00:17:34.327 --> 00:17:35.828
How... how do you know this?

200
00:17:36.203 --> 00:17:37.705
He sent word to me.

201
00:17:39.123 --> 00:17:40.458
To you?

202
00:17:42.835 --> 00:17:44.420
The two of you have been...

203
00:17:45.796 --> 00:17:49.675
plotting without my authority?

204
00:18:52.572 --> 00:18:54.449
Harrenhal is a useful morass.

205
00:18:54.950 --> 00:18:57.827
It will keep Daemon well-occupied
while we strengthen our host

206
00:18:58.119 --> 00:19:00.121
and weaken Rhaenyra's
support on the mainland.

207
00:19:00.205 --> 00:19:02.541
We will deal with it
in the Riverlands in time.

208
00:19:03.166 --> 00:19:06.753
But right now.
Rook's Rest is an easy target

209
00:19:07.546 --> 00:19:08.880
and a worthy effort.

210
00:19:10.507 --> 00:19:13.301
Don't you agree. my king?

211
00:19:28.525 --> 00:19:29.901
Come.

212
00:19:34.031 --> 00:19:35.198
Lord Larys.

213
00:19:39.453 --> 00:19:41.330
I thought I'd look in on you.
Your Grace

214
00:19:41.580 --> 00:19:44.208
after your absence
from the small council.

215
00:19:44.625 --> 00:19:46.418
I feared something was amiss.

216
00:19:47.544 --> 00:19:49.463
You're kind to do so. my lord

217
00:19:49.546 --> 00:19:52.090
but indulgence was my sin.

218
00:19:52.174 --> 00:19:55.344
I ventured into the lamprey pie
at last night's supper.

219
00:19:55.427 --> 00:19:56.887
Too far. I fear.

220
00:20:03.811 --> 00:20:05.521
That is a rich indulgence.

221
00:20:07.147 --> 00:20:08.273
But I believe it is a sin

222
00:20:08.357 --> 00:20:10.192
to deny your appetites.

223
00:20:10.693 --> 00:20:13.529
They are what make us fully alive
as mortal men.

224
00:20:18.325 --> 00:20:20.452
Was anything of note
discussed at the council?

225
00:20:20.953 --> 00:20:22.663
Daemon having seized Harrenhal

226
00:20:22.746 --> 00:20:25.332
and His Grace's
resulting displeasure.

227
00:20:25.541 --> 00:20:28.377
I would've thought you would be
the most aggrieved. my lord.

228
00:20:30.504 --> 00:20:32.423
I see it as a loss
for our greater good.

229
00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:36.677
Dragonstone's attentions
are greatly divided.

230
00:20:36.761 --> 00:20:38.387
First in the Riverlands
and the Gullet

231
00:20:38.471 --> 00:20:39.847
and now the Crownlands.

232
00:20:40.890 --> 00:20:42.808
Ser Criston wins every challenge
he faces there.

233
00:20:42.892 --> 00:20:45.811
That truth alone is like to
incite Rhaenyra's fury.

234
00:20:47.104 --> 00:20:49.231
He's covered himself in glory.
to be sure.

235
00:20:50.650 --> 00:20:52.276
And you must worry for him?

236
00:20:53.736 --> 00:20:55.863
Your sworn sword

237
00:20:56.989 --> 00:21:00.117
on the march.
ever exposed to dragons?

238
00:21:00.201 --> 00:21:01.744
It is a perilous road.

239
00:21:05.331 --> 00:21:07.124
Ser Criston is the Hand of the King.

240
00:21:08.668 --> 00:21:11.003
We should all pray for his victory
and safe return.

241
00:21:12.380 --> 00:21:13.714
Indeed.

242
00:21:23.474 --> 00:21:26.352
If I may be so bold. my queen...

243
00:21:32.734 --> 00:21:34.777
you have not seemed yourself of late.

244
00:21:36.738 --> 00:21:38.907
Only weeks ago.
my lord husband was alive

245
00:21:39.073 --> 00:21:40.617
and the realm was at peace.

246
00:21:41.576 --> 00:21:45.205
Now. I've barely had the hours
to grieve one tragedy

247
00:21:45.288 --> 00:21:46.331
before suffering the next.

248
00:21:46.414 --> 00:21:49.125
I regret if I have not been myself.

249
00:21:53.671 --> 00:21:56.382
I did not know you shared
your lord husband's love

250
00:21:57.258 --> 00:21:58.760
for the histories.

251
00:22:00.595 --> 00:22:03.598
If not his love.
then certainly an abiding interest.

252
00:22:05.475 --> 00:22:07.060
The voices of history guided Viserys.

253
00:22:07.143 --> 00:22:10.397
He knew that his wisdom alone
could only reach so far.

254
00:22:10.522 --> 00:22:12.607
Do you think that is why
he changed his mind

255
00:22:14.401 --> 00:22:15.735
in the end?

256
00:22:17.028 --> 00:22:20.907
No matter how suited he thought
Rhaenyra for the crown

257
00:22:20.991 --> 00:22:25.287
the voices of history. as you say

258
00:22:25.620 --> 00:22:29.249
would have told him how the realm
would react to her succession.

259
00:22:29.332 --> 00:22:30.959
It was impossible to know
what steered his thoughts

260
00:22:31.042 --> 00:22:32.377
in those final hours.

261
00:22:34.087 --> 00:22:35.922
Do you now doubt his intentions?

262
00:22:43.972 --> 00:22:46.224
Rhaenyra's supporters
will believe what they wish.

263
00:22:47.184 --> 00:22:48.602
And so will Aegon's.

264
00:22:50.020 --> 00:22:53.398
The war will be fought. many will die

265
00:22:54.608 --> 00:22:56.902
and the victor will eventually
ascend the throne.

266
00:22:59.154 --> 00:23:02.074
The significance of Viserys's
intentions died with him.

267
00:23:08.872 --> 00:23:10.207
Yes. it did.

268
00:24:47.889 --> 00:24:50.475
It's a touch late to be
stalkin' about a strange castle

269
00:24:50.558 --> 00:24:52.268
putting its people to the sword.

270
00:24:52.602 --> 00:24:53.936
You.

271
00:24:55.021 --> 00:24:56.564
I'm called Alys.

272
00:24:57.523 --> 00:24:58.858
Strong?

273
00:24:58.983 --> 00:25:00.318
Rivers.

274
00:25:01.152 --> 00:25:02.487
A bastard.

275
00:25:02.904 --> 00:25:05.156
Once you get to know me.
you'll find I'm not so bad.

276
00:25:06.324 --> 00:25:08.701
So what are you then?
Some kind of... maester?

277
00:25:08.785 --> 00:25:10.245
In a manner of speaking.

278
00:25:10.829 --> 00:25:14.374
I inherited the duties
after the last one fled in the night.

279
00:25:14.457 --> 00:25:17.460
- Fled? Why?
- Just never settled in.

280
00:25:20.213 --> 00:25:21.631
How are you settling in?

281
00:25:22.882 --> 00:25:26.177
I've come to know the face
of tortured rest well enough.

282
00:25:26.636 --> 00:25:29.973
Sleep can be thin in this place.

283
00:25:31.099 --> 00:25:32.642
What would you know of my sleep?

284
00:25:34.311 --> 00:25:37.147
Harrenhal's been cursed
since its first stone was laid.

285
00:25:38.732 --> 00:25:40.984
Black Harren felled
the grove of weirwood trees

286
00:25:41.234 --> 00:25:42.819
that grew on these lands.

287
00:25:43.278 --> 00:25:45.030
Heart trees. imbued with the spirits

288
00:25:45.113 --> 00:25:47.490
of those who lived
long before he came.

289
00:25:47.574 --> 00:25:49.743
It's said their whispers
can still be heard sometimes.

290
00:25:49.826 --> 00:25:51.203
A midwife's tale.

291
00:25:51.620 --> 00:25:54.748
The very bed you sleep in
was made from such a heart tree.

292
00:25:56.708 --> 00:26:00.253
Have you experienced
anything of note?

293
00:26:00.879 --> 00:26:02.964
You are a strange kind of woman.

294
00:26:03.799 --> 00:26:06.259
I'm no woman at all.
I'm a barn owl.

295
00:26:06.468 --> 00:26:08.470
Cursed to live in human form.

296
00:26:11.306 --> 00:26:13.433
So you've come here
after quarreling with your wife?

297
00:26:14.351 --> 00:26:15.560
What?

298
00:26:16.812 --> 00:26:18.438
You arrive here alone

299
00:26:18.563 --> 00:26:21.566
to claim the castle
and yet send no ravens.

300
00:26:23.902 --> 00:26:26.363
Do you now plan
to make your own claim?

301
00:26:27.030 --> 00:26:28.532
Perhaps to prove yourself to her.

302
00:26:28.615 --> 00:26:31.076
Do not try me
with your insolence. witch.

303
00:26:31.159 --> 00:26:32.578
It's a hard thing. I imagine

304
00:26:32.661 --> 00:26:36.123
to give obeisance to one
who replaced you as heir.

305
00:26:39.126 --> 00:26:40.752
And a woman too. A...

306
00:26:41.378 --> 00:26:43.964
girl child you bounced on your knee.

307
00:26:46.425 --> 00:26:49.261
I mean. does it please you
that her legitimacy is contested?

308
00:26:49.344 --> 00:26:53.182
As you stand here.
with a castle and a dragon

309
00:26:53.932 --> 00:26:56.185
attempting to draw an army of men.

310
00:27:01.357 --> 00:27:02.691
Here. Drink this.

311
00:27:04.860 --> 00:27:05.903
You'll need your sleep

312
00:27:05.986 --> 00:27:07.988
if you're to win this place
to your side.

313
00:27:18.165 --> 00:27:21.669
I now rule my house as regent until
my nephew Benjicot comes of age.

314
00:27:27.007 --> 00:27:29.677
The Brackens are venal cravens

315
00:27:29.885 --> 00:27:33.055
and they must pay for their treachery
against the laws of gods and men.

316
00:27:34.807 --> 00:27:36.225
And against the crown.

317
00:27:36.809 --> 00:27:38.144
Who are you?

318
00:27:38.352 --> 00:27:41.272
Ser Willem Blackwood
of House Blackwood. Your Grace

319
00:27:41.397 --> 00:27:42.732
as I said.

320
00:27:46.903 --> 00:27:48.237
Well met.

321
00:27:49.113 --> 00:27:50.615
What might I do for you?

322
00:27:50.907 --> 00:27:54.285
It was you who summoned me.
Your Grace.

323
00:27:55.119 --> 00:27:57.747
I was given to understand that
you wanted an army.

324
00:27:58.331 --> 00:27:59.874
Well. who doesn't these days?

325
00:28:00.166 --> 00:28:01.959
You Blackwoods certainly
never miss a chance

326
00:28:02.043 --> 00:28:05.088
to bloody your swords. do you?

327
00:28:06.255 --> 00:28:09.342
Some 20 years ago.
my lord bent the knee to King Viserys

328
00:28:09.425 --> 00:28:11.094
and acknowledged
the Princess Rhaenyra

329
00:28:11.177 --> 00:28:12.512
as his rightful heir.

330
00:28:12.762 --> 00:28:14.097
So you fight for this old oath?

331
00:28:14.180 --> 00:28:16.224
Not. of course.
for your thousand-year-old feud

332
00:28:16.307 --> 00:28:17.642
with the Brackens.

333
00:28:19.268 --> 00:28:21.354
I once vied for Queen Rhaenyra's hand

334
00:28:22.438 --> 00:28:23.940
before she wed Ser Laenor.

335
00:28:24.857 --> 00:28:26.442
I always liked her spirit.

336
00:28:27.694 --> 00:28:29.571
She had the true blood of the dragon.

337
00:28:29.696 --> 00:28:32.699
And you're prepared to march
without the leave of your lord...

338
00:28:55.722 --> 00:28:57.098
Your Grace?

339
00:28:59.100 --> 00:29:00.810
And once you and your dragon

340
00:29:00.894 --> 00:29:03.313
bring the queen's justice
to the Brackens

341
00:29:04.314 --> 00:29:05.982
our armies will be yours.

342
00:29:15.700 --> 00:29:17.994
Our lords in the Crownlands
are grousing.

343
00:29:18.245 --> 00:29:20.372
Their herds of livestock
struggle to keep pace

344
00:29:20.455 --> 00:29:22.082
with the dragons'
relentless appetites.

345
00:29:22.165 --> 00:29:23.416
Vhagar's in particular.

346
00:29:23.500 --> 00:29:25.335
They can either provide the crown
what it needs

347
00:29:25.419 --> 00:29:27.587
or we can claim their holdings.

348
00:29:27.712 --> 00:29:29.131
Oh. that would be a relief

349
00:29:29.214 --> 00:29:31.508
as we have no more coin
to lend to the effort.

350
00:29:31.591 --> 00:29:34.344
Resources are certainly
growing no more plentiful

351
00:29:34.428 --> 00:29:35.470
in the face of the blockade.

352
00:29:35.554 --> 00:29:37.597
The demand on the blacksmiths.
armorers and tanners for equipment

353
00:29:37.681 --> 00:29:39.766
has only grown apace
with Ser Criston's army.

354
00:29:40.058 --> 00:29:41.852
Well. Cole's done splendidly.
at the least

355
00:29:42.185 --> 00:29:44.104
turning every castle
and army he's faced

356
00:29:44.187 --> 00:29:46.273
including Duskendale.
gods bless him.

357
00:29:47.316 --> 00:29:49.026
The Kingmaker. they're calling him.

358
00:29:49.318 --> 00:29:51.570
And with Aemond and Vhagar
also at the ready

359
00:29:51.653 --> 00:29:53.238
we are a formidable opponent.

360
00:29:55.032 --> 00:29:56.492
You bore me.

361
00:29:59.536 --> 00:30:01.038
You all bore me.

362
00:30:17.596 --> 00:30:21.141
Perhaps Ser Criston will be able
to procure more livestock

363
00:30:21.225 --> 00:30:22.309
through his campaign.

364
00:30:22.393 --> 00:30:24.937
Any coin we can save
will be a welcome bounty.

365
00:30:34.947 --> 00:30:35.990
What are you doing here?

366
00:30:36.282 --> 00:30:37.825
Where are your father's books?

367
00:30:38.033 --> 00:30:39.410
I ordered them removed.

368
00:30:39.910 --> 00:30:42.746
With no thought to the centuries
of knowledge in those pages.

369
00:30:49.336 --> 00:30:50.755
Your Grace.

370
00:30:52.590 --> 00:30:55.092
I removed them. I didn't burn them.

371
00:31:00.473 --> 00:31:01.515
What is it?

372
00:31:01.891 --> 00:31:03.768
They don't care what I think.

373
00:31:06.938 --> 00:31:08.981
- Who. Aegon?
- My council.

374
00:31:09.315 --> 00:31:11.442
Cole. Aemond.
They pursue their campaign

375
00:31:11.525 --> 00:31:13.569
without seeking my aid.
or even my thoughts.

376
00:31:16.948 --> 00:31:18.241
What thoughts would you have?

377
00:31:20.243 --> 00:31:21.577
I'm the king.

378
00:31:25.039 --> 00:31:27.792
Do you think simply wearing the crown
imbues you with wisdom?

379
00:31:34.632 --> 00:31:37.510
Those men at your council table

380
00:31:38.928 --> 00:31:40.388
earned their seats.

381
00:31:41.931 --> 00:31:44.601
It was my hope that once enthroned

382
00:31:44.934 --> 00:31:47.270
you would honor the burden
of your new duties

383
00:31:47.562 --> 00:31:48.896
be silent

384
00:31:49.105 --> 00:31:52.191
and strive to learn from
the more studied minds around you.

385
00:31:54.360 --> 00:31:56.613
In the hope that you might be
half the king your father was.

386
00:31:58.990 --> 00:32:00.867
- Tread carefully.
- Or what?

387
00:32:03.161 --> 00:32:05.538
You'll hang me.
as you did your ratcatchers?

388
00:32:06.206 --> 00:32:08.416
Or have me banished.
as you did your Hand?

389
00:32:10.335 --> 00:32:11.544
I ruled

390
00:32:11.711 --> 00:32:14.005
in your father's absence
throughout his long illness

391
00:32:14.089 --> 00:32:16.800
and Otto Hightower was
as cunning a statesman as ever lived.

392
00:32:16.883 --> 00:32:21.846
You should humbly be seeking
our opinions and counsel.

393
00:32:24.516 --> 00:32:26.434
You have no idea the sacrifices
that were made

394
00:32:26.518 --> 00:32:28.186
to put you on that throne.

395
00:32:33.400 --> 00:32:34.442
Wha...

396
00:32:36.570 --> 00:32:38.363
What would you have me do. Mother?

397
00:32:40.532 --> 00:32:42.409
Do simply what is needed of you...

398
00:32:44.619 --> 00:32:45.912
nothing.

399
00:33:16.276 --> 00:33:17.653
On your feet!

400
00:33:19.571 --> 00:33:21.031
To Rook's Rest!

401
00:33:22.658 --> 00:33:23.992
To battle!

402
00:33:29.373 --> 00:33:30.916
It's broad daylight.

403
00:33:31.291 --> 00:33:34.545
We must hold here and ready ourselves
to lay siege at nightfall.

404
00:33:35.087 --> 00:33:38.048
We shall move now and strike by day.
They will not expect it.

405
00:33:38.298 --> 00:33:41.468
They will not expect it
because it is fucking madness.

406
00:33:43.887 --> 00:33:46.432
Did you forget the little encounter
we had on the road to Rosby?

407
00:33:47.099 --> 00:33:48.434
I did not.

408
00:33:50.269 --> 00:33:52.855
Dragonstone and their dragons
are just across the bay.

409
00:33:54.607 --> 00:33:56.483
What?
Grown tired of living. have you?

410
00:33:57.651 --> 00:33:59.111
Are you afraid. Ser?

411
00:34:00.321 --> 00:34:02.448
Worse. I'm rational.

412
00:34:04.575 --> 00:34:05.993
We advance.

413
00:34:27.056 --> 00:34:28.224
I see no other choice.

414
00:34:28.516 --> 00:34:30.726
- We need to send a dragon.
- Where?

415
00:34:36.148 --> 00:34:39.777
To support the war that your vassals
have been fighting in your absence

416
00:34:40.319 --> 00:34:41.654
Your Grace.

417
00:34:42.905 --> 00:34:45.908
Cole's host has grown
since riding abroad.

418
00:34:45.992 --> 00:34:48.286
He raised the levies
of both Rosby and Stokeworth

419
00:34:48.369 --> 00:34:51.247
and. with their combined strength.
sacked Duskendale.

420
00:34:51.330 --> 00:34:52.790
Duskendale?

421
00:34:52.915 --> 00:34:54.292
The city has fallen.

422
00:34:54.876 --> 00:34:56.544
Many Darklyn men declared for Aegon.

423
00:34:56.753 --> 00:34:58.463
Those who refused
were put to the sword.

424
00:34:58.546 --> 00:34:59.881
What of my father?

425
00:35:00.381 --> 00:35:01.799
He kept his oath.

426
00:35:02.508 --> 00:35:03.593
Cole took his head for it.

427
00:35:06.596 --> 00:35:09.265
Where have you been. these last days?

428
00:35:09.599 --> 00:35:11.684
You vanished
without so much as a word.

429
00:35:12.810 --> 00:35:15.563
Well. I apologize for my absence
and the secrecy

430
00:35:15.855 --> 00:35:17.440
but such was necessary.

431
00:35:18.691 --> 00:35:20.026
I went to King's Landing.

432
00:35:21.820 --> 00:35:23.029
To what possible end?

433
00:35:23.112 --> 00:35:25.657
To meet Queen Alicent
and sue for peace.

434
00:35:25.740 --> 00:35:28.451
- You saw Alicent?
- Yes. I did.

435
00:35:28.576 --> 00:35:30.703
You could've been taken or slain!

436
00:35:30.787 --> 00:35:34.082
I inherited 80 years of peace
from my father.

437
00:35:34.833 --> 00:35:36.126
Before I was to end it

438
00:35:36.459 --> 00:35:38.503
I needed to know
that there was no other path.

439
00:35:41.965 --> 00:35:43.299
And now I do.

440
00:35:46.928 --> 00:35:48.805
Only one choice remains to me.

441
00:35:49.222 --> 00:35:52.475
Either I win my claim or die.

442
00:35:55.061 --> 00:35:56.563
We stand at the ready.

443
00:35:58.190 --> 00:36:00.275
Cole's victories
have only emboldened him.

444
00:36:00.358 --> 00:36:02.194
He marches on Rook's Rest.

445
00:36:02.694 --> 00:36:04.321
His host was just hours away

446
00:36:04.404 --> 00:36:06.156
when Lord Staunton's
ravens took wing.

447
00:36:06.239 --> 00:36:08.742
Why Rook's Rest?
After Duskendale?

448
00:36:09.117 --> 00:36:11.077
It is but a small coastal keep.

449
00:36:11.161 --> 00:36:13.872
'Cause Lord Staunton
is a member of this council.

450
00:36:14.456 --> 00:36:16.958
And because his castle
is small and vulnerable

451
00:36:17.042 --> 00:36:18.377
and there for the taking.

452
00:36:18.627 --> 00:36:21.171
Cole knows we have no army
on the mainland.

453
00:36:21.254 --> 00:36:23.632
- He is brazen.
- He is daring us to act.

454
00:36:23.715 --> 00:36:26.259
We need to send a dragon.

455
00:36:33.600 --> 00:36:37.104
There are those who have mistaken
my caution for weakness.

456
00:36:42.234 --> 00:36:43.777
Let that be their undoing.

457
00:36:45.070 --> 00:36:47.364
- I will go.
- My queen...

458
00:36:47.656 --> 00:36:50.409
- You cannot.
- I will not lose dragons to war

459
00:36:50.492 --> 00:36:51.535
whilst I hide here in my castle.

460
00:36:51.618 --> 00:36:54.830
Our allies raise their banners
for you. Mother.

461
00:36:54.913 --> 00:36:56.248
Yes. they do.

462
00:36:56.957 --> 00:36:59.835
If you die. all is lost.

463
00:37:00.210 --> 00:37:01.378
- Send me.
- No.

464
00:37:01.462 --> 00:37:03.547
I will burn Cole's lines and
withdraw before King's Landing

465
00:37:03.630 --> 00:37:05.424
- could even raise the alarm.
- You lack the experience.

466
00:37:08.510 --> 00:37:11.180
You must send me. Your Grace.

467
00:37:13.015 --> 00:37:16.101
Meleys is your largest dragon
and no stranger to battle.

468
00:37:19.271 --> 00:37:20.814
I will meet Cole.

469
00:38:29.842 --> 00:38:33.388
I wish only to fight for you.
for your claim and mine.

470
00:38:33.596 --> 00:38:34.931
I...

471
00:38:36.558 --> 00:38:38.309
There's something
I need to tell you. Jace.

472
00:38:40.728 --> 00:38:43.982
Something I should've told you

473
00:38:44.190 --> 00:38:46.276
when you first became heir
to the throne.

474
00:38:47.527 --> 00:38:52.323
It's a secret that Viserys told me
when he named me his successor.

475
00:38:53.825 --> 00:38:56.786
And it has passed from king to heir

476
00:38:57.829 --> 00:39:00.123
since Aegon the Conqueror's time.

477
00:39:08.715 --> 00:39:12.761
I never told you because I was unsure
that I believed it myself.

478
00:39:14.095 --> 00:39:17.265
The Targaryen
who sits the Iron Throne

479
00:39:18.016 --> 00:39:20.101
is not just a king or a queen.

480
00:39:20.435 --> 00:39:22.270
They are a Protector.

481
00:39:26.650 --> 00:39:30.195
Ordained to lead the Seven Kingdoms.
to strengthen them

482
00:39:32.781 --> 00:39:36.535
and to unite them
against a common foe.

483
00:39:41.248 --> 00:39:44.251
Viserys chose me to succeed him.

484
00:39:45.669 --> 00:39:47.754
He held to this
the whole of his life.

485
00:39:53.885 --> 00:39:59.224
My father believed that I. alone.
was meant to be this Protector.

486
00:40:00.183 --> 00:40:02.853
They're 1.400. 1.500-strong
at least. my lord.

487
00:40:04.730 --> 00:40:08.150
But to unite the realm.
I had to send the dragons to war.

488
00:40:16.992 --> 00:40:20.079
The horrors I have just loosed
cannot be for a crown alone.

489
00:40:22.706 --> 00:40:24.708
That is why I must believe

490
00:40:24.792 --> 00:40:27.252
what Viserys told me
when he named me his heir.

491
00:40:27.920 --> 00:40:29.755
What Jaehaerys had told him.

492
00:40:31.256 --> 00:40:33.092
And what I will now tell you.

493
00:40:36.095 --> 00:40:37.429
What is it?

494
00:40:43.477 --> 00:40:45.563
Aegon the Conqueror's dream.

495
00:40:47.898 --> 00:40:51.277
He called it
"The Song of Ice and Fire."

496
00:41:01.328 --> 00:41:02.413
Loose!

497
00:41:02.496 --> 00:41:03.622
New rank!

498
00:41:04.957 --> 00:41:06.208
Loose!

499
00:41:06.792 --> 00:41:07.835
New rank!

500
00:41:08.502 --> 00:41:11.380
Loose! New rank!

501
00:41:16.052 --> 00:41:17.094
Push it!

502
00:41:17.887 --> 00:41:19.180
Dragon!

503
00:41:19.263 --> 00:41:21.641
- Dragon!
- Dragon!

504
00:41:25.937 --> 00:41:28.356
To the Seven Hells with you. Cole!

505
00:41:29.023 --> 00:41:31.234
You may as well have sounded horns
to announce our coming!

506
00:41:31.317 --> 00:41:33.277
Order the Darklyn levies
to break off and move ahead.

507
00:41:33.361 --> 00:41:35.196
We must keep
the dragon's attention divided.

508
00:41:35.279 --> 00:41:37.240
- Make the signal.
- What signal?

509
00:41:37.490 --> 00:41:39.033
All is going to plan.

510
00:43:11.376 --> 00:43:13.211
Forward. Sunfyre!

511
00:43:13.837 --> 00:43:15.213
Faster!

512
00:43:16.006 --> 00:43:17.758
- Dragon!
- Dragon!

513
00:43:17.841 --> 00:43:18.926
Whose dragon is that?

514
00:43:19.843 --> 00:43:21.470
His Grace. the king's.

515
00:43:22.554 --> 00:43:24.640
This was your secret plot. Cole?

516
00:43:24.806 --> 00:43:26.558
For the king himself to lay ambush

517
00:43:26.642 --> 00:43:28.727
- and mayhaps die in the attempt?
- No!

518
00:43:28.810 --> 00:43:30.687
Loose more signal arrows!

519
00:43:34.316 --> 00:43:36.777
Stalwart men of House Targaryen

520
00:43:37.694 --> 00:43:40.072
your king has joined you!

521
00:43:41.198 --> 00:43:44.201
Hold to your courage!
Hold to your wits!

522
00:43:44.284 --> 00:43:47.371
For the Seven have blessed
and shielded this host

523
00:43:47.454 --> 00:43:48.914
with divine purpose!

524
00:43:49.206 --> 00:43:52.251
For the one true king. Aegon!

525
00:43:52.459 --> 00:43:54.878
Advance!

526
00:44:02.887 --> 00:44:04.388
Where are you. Aemond?

527
00:44:19.987 --> 00:44:21.530
<i>Dracarys!</i>

528
00:45:00.445 --> 00:45:01.821
Another one there!

529
00:45:02.530 --> 00:45:04.449
Send a volley to those Rosby men!

530
00:45:04.699 --> 00:45:06.617
Give them no quarter!

531
00:45:16.169 --> 00:45:18.004
We'd best get you to cover. my lord.

532
00:46:07.053 --> 00:46:08.597
Thank the gods!

533
00:46:10.182 --> 00:46:11.725
<i>Dracarys!</i>

534
00:46:16.980 --> 00:46:19.316
No! No!

535
00:46:38.627 --> 00:46:40.003
Your Grace!

536
00:51:46.604 --> 00:51:48.397
Fall in behind me!

537
00:51:49.816 --> 00:51:51.401
Into the breach!

538
00:52:23.308 --> 00:52:26.060
The king has fallen.
We must find him.

539
00:53:15.777 --> 00:53:17.154
Aemond!

540
00:53:32.711 --> 00:53:33.754
Where's His Grace?
